  "market_context": "The analyst presents a clear bearish structure on EURUSD 1H where price consistently makes lower highs (LH) and lower lows (LL), breaks structural swing highs downward, and respects green-labeled supply zones above price action.",
  "key_observation": "Price respects supply areas and breaks structures to the downside, forming a perfect downtrend with identifiable swing highs/lows and newly formed supply zones after each break of structure.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst defines an ideal downtrend as price making lower highs and lower lows while breaking structural levels to the downside.",
    "Step 2: He explains that each break of a structural level to the downside automatically creates a new supply area (zone).",
    "Step 3: He emphasizes that as long as price remains below the most recent swing high (LH), the downtrend is intact and only selling is considered.",
    "Step 4: He shows the EURUSD 1H chart (frame f005) with five green rectangles aligned to swing highs, illustrating supply zones and the descending white trendline confirming lower highs/lows.",
    "Step 5: He contrasts this ideal case with imperfect trends later, but for this case, confirms the market is clearly in control of sellers."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "In an ideal downtrend, focus solely on selling near supply zones (swing highs) while price stays below the most recent swing high; structure validation requires a close below the level, not just a wick.",
